## Defining the writer settings for a single node
This feature allows to define custom writer settings for an element or attribute in the data structure.

> Important

The custom writer settings of a single schema node take precedence over the writer settings common to all nodes.

The functionality is useful, for example, when you want to set the alignment of the data in the fixed structure records of a flat file.

- Open the Flat File Writer resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources.](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)

- Select the required element from the panel on the left.

-  Select the **Settings **tab on the right.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)	

- In the **Node name alias **field, enter the name that you want to assign to the header record.

- Select the **Enable **option if you want to enable writing the contents of this node.

- Select the **Add record header **option if you want to enable the generation of the header within a record.

*(optional) *If you selected the **Add record header **checkbox, select the **Use alias **check box to use the name entered in the corresponding field in the header as a node, instead of the name of the selected field.

- From the **Assigned variable **drop-down menu, select the required variable. The system assigns the value of the node to the variable.

> Tip

Variables are useful, for example, to compose the output filename.

- In the **Node formatting **panel on the right, enable the **Custom formatting **toggle to define the custom writer settings for the selected field, instead of using the general writer settings.

> Note

For more information, see [Defining the node formatting settings](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-flat-file-writer-settings-tab#defining-the-node-formatting-settings) below.

### Defining the node formatting settings
This feature allows to define the custom writer settings for the selected field, instead of using the general writer settings.

> Note

For more information on the general writer settings, see: [DT3 Flat File Writer - Global Actions](/doxee-platform/docs/4-dt3-flat-file-writer-global-actions).

- In the **Node formatting **panel on the right, enable the **Custom formatting **toggle.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Alignment**

Select the alignment of the data in the fixed structure records of the flat file:

**Left: **Align the value to the left, adding a filler character to the right.

- **Right: **Align the value to the right, adding a filler character to the left.

**Text qualifier**

Select the separator character that you want to use to delimit fields containing text strings. The available options are:

- **None**

- **'**

- **"**

**Indent level**

*(optional) *Define the custom indentation level for this field.

**Delimited**

Select this option to define the writer settings using a separator character.

From the corresponding drop-down menu, select the separator character that you want to use. The available options are:

- **None **

- **Tab**

- **|**

**Fixed**

Select this option to define the writer settings using a fixed-size field.

- In the **Length **field, enter the dimension of the field.

- From the **Padding **drop-down menu, select the padding character that you want to use. The available options are:

**Zero **

- **Space**

> Note

If a field has a fewer characters than its fixed length, padding characters allow to reach the fixed length.
